The paper deals with task scheduling and resource allocation in a heterogeneous cellular network, which is a topic related to network architecture and communication protocols. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes an auction-based incentive scheme, which involves game theory and mechanism design, making cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) likely sub-categories as well. The use of cloud edge computing and computation offloading also suggests cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves optimization and algorithm design, which falls under cs.IT (Information Theory).
